<TITLE> Stocks gain sharply in midday trade </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 9 (bdnews24.com)The country's prime bourse continued its bull run from the previous week to open upbeat on the first trading day of the week. Market observers said declaration of dividends by several companies boosted investor confidence. The DSE general index rose sharply from start of trade Sunday to cross the 3000 mark. At 11.48 am, the benchmark DGEN or general index was up 19.36 points or 0.64 percent to 3010.73, while the DSI or all share price index was at 2543.05, up 15.04 points or 0.59 percent. Turnover stood at Tk 1.61 billion earned from trading of 9,972,552 shares. Gainers outnumbered losers 134 to 77 with some six issues remaining unchanged. Banks, dominating the turnover board, saw their share prices falling while pharmaceuticals and mutual funds gained. Top of the turnover board, AB Bank fell to Tk 3323 from Thursday's Tk 3434.7 due to profit taking. Uttara Bank also declined on profit taking selling at Tk 4850 down from Tk 4996.25 the previous week. Pharmaceuticals major, Square Pharma rose on buying pressure, selling up at Tk 1669.25 from Thursday's Tk 3527.25. Dutch Bangla Bank fell to Tk 13,128 from its previous closing of Tk 13,726. Grameen Mutual Fund One advanced to Tk 133.70 from Thursday's closing price of Tk 130.10. Other banking scrips on the turnover board that lost were IFIC, NCC and BRAC Bank. Lafarge Surma Cement and AIMS 1st mutual fund gained. bdn
